&lt;p&gt;Long Meadow Ranch has an exciting opportunity to join our close-knit Mountain Estate winemaking team for Harvest 2026. Long Meadow Ranch is a family­-owned and operated producer and purveyor of world­-class wine and food that is economically successful and socially responsible using diversified, sustainable, and organic farming methods. Long Meadow Ranch produces award-winning wines, ciders, handcrafted extra virgin olive oils, grass­-fed beef, eggs, and heirloom fruits and vegetables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Harvest Cellar Worker&lt;/strong&gt; to join the wine production team for Harvest 2026.&amp;nbsp; This is a temporary position expected to begin in August or September and end at the completion of Harvest (including Olives) in November or December, depending on the season.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;You will work closely with our small team, including the winemakers, and be exposed to all sides of harvest from receiving and processing fruit to managing juice and wine all the way to the barrel.&amp;nbsp; We are committed to teaching aspiring wine professionals about all aspects of winemaking in a fun and safe team environment.&amp;nbsp; If you have a strong work ethic and passion for learning about wine, this is the next great opportunity for you.&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
